":"1186","1209":"1209","1270":"1270","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Walcot, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Walcot, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Weobley, Herefordshire, England":"Weobley, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Laurence","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Marcel, Normand, Patrice, Raymonde, Serge.","English: variant of   Lawrence  .","French: from the female personal name <i>Laurence</i>, a feminine equivalent of   Lawrence  . Compare   Larance  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Lawrence","meanings":["English: from the Middle English and Old French personal name <i>Lorens</i>, <i>Laurence</i>, from Latin <i>Laurentius</i> ‘man from <i>Laurentum</i>’, a place in Italy probably named from its laurels or bay trees. The name was borne by a Christian saint who was martyred at Rome in the 3rd century  AD ; he enjoyed a considerable cult throughout Europe, with consequent popularity of the personal name (French <i>Laurent</i>, Italian, Spanish <i>Lorenzo</i>, Catalan <i>Llorenç</i>, Portuguese <i>Lourenço</i>, German <i>Laurenz</i>, Polish <i>Wawrzyniec</i>, etc.). In Britain this is a common name from the 12th century, with pet forms such as   Law  ,   Low  ,   Lawrie  ,   Laurie  ,   Larry  ,   Larkin  , all of which are represented in surnames. There was also a feminine form <i>Laurencia</i> which may have given rise to the English surname. The surname is also borne by Jews among whom it is presumably an Americanized form of one or more similar (like-sounding) Ashkenazic surnames. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed many cognates from other languages, e.g. German   Lorenz  , and also their patronymics and other derivatives, e.g. Slovenian <b>Lavrenčič</b> and <b>Lovrenčič</b> (patronymics from <i>Lavrencij</i> and <i>Lovrenc</i>, equivalents of <i>Lawrence</i>), Polish   Wawrzyniak  . Compare   Larrance  ,   Laurence  ,   Lawerence  ,   Lieurance  , and   Lowrance  ."]},{"name":"Larance","meanings":["Altered form of French   Laurence  ."]}]},{"name":"Mazeline","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A female name softened down from Magdalen. Compare the French Madeleine and Madelon; the Italian Maddalena; and the Spanish Madelena."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mazeline Laurence was born in 1190, in Weobley, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Laurence de Marbury in 1209, in Hereford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter."},"et":{"1190–":"1190–Surnud","1186–Male":"1186–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1210–Male":"1210–Surnud","1212–Female":"1212–Surnud","1214–Male":"1214–Surnud","1190–Female":"1190–Surnud","1190":"1190","1214":"1214","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1186":"1186","1209":"1209","1270":"1270","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Walcot, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Walcot, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Weobley, Herefordshire, England":"Weobley, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1190–":"1190–Kuollut","1186–Male":"1186–Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1210–Male":"1210–Kuollut","1212–Female":"1212–Kuollut","1214–Male":"1214–Kuollut","1190–Female":"1190–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1214":"1214","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1186":"1186","1209":"1209","1270":"1270","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Walcot, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Walcot, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Weobley, Herefordshire, England":"Weobley, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"}